howdy
-----

Displays XKCD comics or your own images in the terminal.

Usage: howdy [OPTIONS]

Options:
  -d, --directory DIR    Serve a random image from the specified directory
  -f, --file FILE        Convert a given file
  -i, --id ID            Fetch and convert XKCD comic with the given ID
  -b, --braille          Use braille characters for higher resolution
  -s, --symbols STRING   String with allowed symbols
  -g, --grayscale        Disable color output
  -w, --width WIDTH      Set the image width
  -h, --height HEIGHT    Set the image height
      --direct           Display image directly in terminal
      --help             Print this help text

If no options are provided, howdy fetches the latest XKCD comic.


EXAMPLES

```
# Prints XKCD comic #599 directly using viu
howdy --id 599 --direct
```

```
# Prints the latest XKCD comic with braille symbols and fixed width
howdy --braille --width 100
```

```
# Prints a random picture from the provided path using the default symbols
howdy --directory ~/Pictures/Anime
```

```
# Prints the selected picture only using the "9" character
howdy --file ~/Pictures/Anime/cirno.png --symbols 9
```

INSTALL

```
git clone https://github.com/birabittoh/howdy.git
cd howdy
go build && mv howdy ~/.local/bin
```


